awards.title: 2014 Blueprints: Holmes Hall Freshman Challenge
awards.awarder: University of Hawaii, at Manoa, College of Engineering
awards.summary: My team won first place in the 2014 Blueprints: Holmes Hall Freshman Challenge. The objective was to get a tennis ball from the third floor of the building down to the second floor within a designated area. Our team designed a system to transfer the ball using tri-fold poster boards to guided the ball off the balcony of the third floor down into a duct vent. The duct vent lead to the second floor and we used a bed sheet to guide the ball into the designated area.
